title._content: Surfing lessons in Cornwall under summer skies

description._content: ID number: UK3078 Photographer: Alexander Stewart Date: 7 July 1945 Place: England Flight Lieutenant H G Winders of Coolangatta, Qld (left), who gave surfboard riding exhibitions at Newquay, Cornwall, with Miss Joy Nichols of London (centre) and Mrs Esme Sanderson, of London. Surf riding and swimming, a rare sport in England, attracted keen interest during a two day aquatic carnival by RAAF personnel on leave at an ACF leave hostel at Newquay from 7 July to 9 July 1945. Rights Info: No known copyright restrictions. This photograph is from the Australian War Memorial's collection www.awm.gov.au Persistent URL: www.awm.gov.au/collection/UK3078
